ri; font-size:9pt">ww.public-standards.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/CSPL-response-to-the-Whistleblowing-Commission-consultation1-v3.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Committee on Standards in Public Life Fifth Biennial Survey of Public Attitudes 2012. Available at: http://www.public-standards.gov.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/Annual-plan-13-14.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn21"></a><a href="#_ftnref21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> http://www.public-standards.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CSPL-survey-2012-WEB-VERSION.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn22"></a><a href="#_ftnref22">[22]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> http://cdn.yougov.com/cumulus_uploads/document/syrhatyofp/Trust_trends_Nov_2012.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn23"></a><a href="#_ftnref23">[23]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> http://www.comres.c</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">o.uk/poll/1021/bbc-news-public-trust-in-the-police.htm</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn24"></a><a href="#_ftnref24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> http://www.public-standards.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Standards_Matter.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn25"></a><a href="#_ftnref25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> The Leveson Inquiry, executive summary, paragraph 89.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn26"></a><a href="#_ftnref26">[26]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> The ethical issues arising from the relationsh